The staff people are always polite and courteous.  It's a very busy location and they are juggling a lot, and constantly multi-tasking; however they remain calm and polite.  I do find that this location is too busy for its geographic space.  It's hard to find parking to simply return the car. <Review>I work remotely but do a bit of local travel using a rental car.   There is nothing better than having an Enterprise Car Rental a few blocks away.

< pictures>
None<//pictures>
< Text>
C'est magnifique!! Ambience, excellent service and food. You have a wonderful view of the Mission across the street ,also great for people watching. Very romantic setting, which was perfect for celebrating our anniversary. Also good for small groups.

Currently, due to COVID, patio dining only. You must wear a mask, menus are disposable and all staff exercises all protocols. Tables are spaced 6-8 feet apart.

A reservation is recommended, as patio seated is limited. There is street parking, or use the parking lot behind restaurant, which is a little past the street entrance. Go past the entrance to lot, then there is a walkway to reach check in and patio.

This is an upscale restaurant with casual vibe. Although indoor dining is currently closed, the decor and vibe is definitely French, including lighting, art and collection of sculpture lining the shelves of the walls. It is intimate setting that is quite Parisian.

Extensive wine list, sold by glass, split or bottles. California, French, American, Australia and New Zealand vineyards of sparkling wine, champagne, burgundy, bordeaux, merlot, Malbec, cabernets including Tattinger, Piper Sonoma, Pouilly-Fuisse, JFJ and others. Corkage fee $20, and vintages can change due to availability.

Starters include pate, brie and fruit, escargot baked in garlic sauce, stuffed mushrooms, frog legs in wine sauce and french onion soup. We chose escargot and Mushroom Farci. Escargot was very tender, and garlic not overpowering. The mushroom had an excellent flavour, shrimp was succulent.

For entrees, you have choice of petite plate or full dinner of chicken, steak, lamb, fish, shrimp or salmon. The difference is for petit plate either/or potatoes or vegetable medley, full entree has both. The petit dinner is great for small appetite, but if you're hungry get the full entree!

Recommended are Beef Bourguigon and Petite Atlantic Salmon. Bourguigon is full of flavour, with slight hint of red wine sauce. My husband was quite pleased at his melt in your mouth goodness. Vegetable medley of yellow squash, carrot and asparagus paired very well with salmon. Just right amount of dill, it was magnificent.

Make sure you leave room for dessert. Because it was our anniversary, we received a complimentary chocolate ice cream with strawberries (topped with candle), but we also enjoyed cherries jubilee. Note about jubilee -- due to health regulations, they do not prepare the dish at table, it is brought to table after it is prepared in kitchen. One order will feed two!

I recommend this for the ambiance, service and patio experience. It is centrally located, and as mentioned, wonderful for romantic dinner or people watching at lunch. We will visit again when COVID protocols allow indoor experience. There are other items on men we want to try! Bon appetit!<//Text>

<review>Like the swallows for which it is named, this country French bistro serving haute Parisian cuisine is certain to delight even the most discerning convive. The family-run gem serving meticulously prepared dishes from original French recipes delivers heavenly flavors from its modest kitchen. From the peppercorn b√©arnaise on the expertly prepared filet to the red wine reduction on the bourguignon, and from the cherry glac√© on the duck to the dill b√©chamel on the salmon, each sauce pairs perfectly with its protein. The delightfully creamy mashed potato and thoughtfully varied garden vegetable accompaniments carry forward each flavor without distracting from the main course. Start with the hot bacon salad and end with the berry custard or cherries jubilee flamb√©. Don't hesitate to sample the intentionally curated wine list, expertly paired upon request. While the food alone is motivation enough to return, the personal service is the icing on the cake. The ambiance of dining in a friend's garden creates a relaxed setting. Unlike the swallows, one is advised to make more than an annual pilgrimage.<//review><pics>None</pics><resp>None</resp><GmapID>0x80dcf1e6e39457ef:0x2202abbc7b6afb3e<//GmapID></record>

Delicious appetizers & entrees. Service was fantastic. Family owned business. I've had a number of dishes here and all have been  well prepared, from the steaks, duck or rack of lamb to the mushrooms, frog legs, French onion, or escargot.  Wonderful date night near the old San Juan mission.  Cozy lil restaurant with a European flair, a must try in my opinion. Oh, don't forget the deserts; tort for chocolate lovers, berry filled creme brulee or a Carmel sauce sundae. Of course there's more I haven't had a chance to try. <Review>One of the few five star ratings I have given as nothing could have been improved.

One of the truly European restaurants my wife and I have had the pleasure of dining in in the states. After moving to the states in 2003 we yearned for European dining, high quality food not large quantity, a table that was ours for hours while lingering over an excellent meal, service that was always there but not intrusive, etc.

Ali has brought it all together. Ali and I found common ground in that we both attended school in Switzerland. That shows in his menus, choice if sides, and presentation.

Meals, bottle of wine, desert, coffee, and  aperitif only $130 with tip. A bargain for the quality, service and atmosphere.</Review>< pictures>

< text>
I bought the wrong coffee brand last night and came in today around the same time to ask if I can return it without the receipt using the same credit card that was purchased with or if I could get an exchange for a different item. The cashier said that she couldn't do anything without the receipt but that I could ask the manager named Alex. I proceeded to ask Alex if I could exchange it for a different item because I had lost the receipt he then looked at me up and down as if to assess me and ask me why don't I have the receipt, what happened to it and what time did I buy the coffee at. He looked at me like I was plotting to scam the store somehow. It made me feel really uncomfortable to be treated this way by manager in front of other customers who were all looking. He sat there contemplating what he was going to say but ended up telling me no he can't help me because I don't have the receipt and as I was walking away he said that it's because of covid he couldn't return it. But just 2 minutes before that the cashier and him both told me that without the receipt they can't do a return 2 minutes later it's because of covid. All he had to say was that he couldn't do anything without the receipt but for him to sit there and ask me what happened to the receipt why don't I have it and what time did I buy the coffee at was unnecessary since he wasn't planning on doing anything about it. Very very poor management customer service.</text>

<Name>Jean-Paul Lederer< /Name></record>

<UserId.>117330972020094383131<//UserId.>< username>
Amanda Mc<//username>
< Time>
1583513667678<//Time>
<rate>1< /rate>< review>
One of the things that I love about San Clemente is how it's a medium-sized town that manages to keep a bit of that small town feel. This Albertsons is great because you get that small town feel as you walk around. It's not huge and open like some grocery stores and you get to know the cashier's a little more because of that.

Now to the reason that this location has the rating it has... I've never felt more offput, unheard, and disrespected by a manager before. I purchased something that was on a deal. I thought there was only one kind for this product, but apparently there are two. They were out of the one that was on deal and I ended up grabbing the other one and purchasing it.

After looking at my receipt I saw the price and went to stand in line with the manager. She'd just seen me purchase this product, she had to swipe her card on the register.

She grabs the paper as she had no clue what the deals were. And then she says she has to go back to the section and check the items. I was a bit confused because I'd already waited ten minutes to talk to her and she looked like she had everything she needed. She insisted she needed to go back as it was policy and I just said sure. She came back ten minutes later. Now I'm twenty minutes behind schedule and I have friends waiting on me. But, it was fine, we're almost all sorted.

She says, dripping condescension, you purchased the product that was not on sale. You grabbed from the top, not the bottom. Now I'm confused because I had no idea that there two types of this product. But, my mistake. It's fine.

"Do you know if you have the right product in the back?"

"I don't know, I don't work for the meat department."

"Well can I just switch these out for the correct product and get refunded the difference?"

"Sorry, it's store policy not to accept returns on perishables."

"So, I'm just stuck with this? You literally just saw me purchase them."

"I can't do any more for you"

Now, thirty minutes later, I drive up the hill to the other Albertsons and within 3 minutes if entering the store I have the right meat and the money back.

I have no idea what store policy she was talking about but I guarantee you I will set foot into that store again. A five minute, in and out, trip to the store became a forthy minute, wholly unnecessary, debacle.

I'll be sending a detailed email to corporate about the situation.<//review>

< Text>
I have been to Jack & Charlie's about a dozen times. Yesterday's lunch (2/3/20) was the first substandard meal/service that we've had. The entrees were still delicious, but we had to track down the waiter (we had never seen him working there previously) because he never checked if our meal was ok (condiments were needed for the burgers). Then we ordered the banana cake for dessert. It was delicious as long as we didn't eat the bottom, which was burnt. We showed the very black, nasty tasting crust to our waiter who basically told us oh well too bad and handed us the bill. Waiters at most reputable restaurants would have taken it off of our bill. He did not offer this so we took it out of his tip instead. I'm sure we will be back again, but hopefully the experience well be back to the usual excellence.<//Text>

<user>104016455661588777717<//user>< Review>
Jack & Charlie's is in the basement of Visalia old jail house. It's quaint like something out of the roaring 20's except in today's standards. There's a red rose or red carnation on each table and you are seated at a table with white table cloth with nice silverware place settings and cloth napkins. It's very classy and brings you back to an era that has been long gone.
Service is very good and the food is good. They do have a bar area that makes fantastic drinks.< /Review>

Update:

Greg, the owner, called me immediately after my review and invited me back for another chance to experience his restaurant.

He was timely with our drink orders, and made it a point to ask us if we wanted water, down to bottles or tap, and what kind of bottled. We didn‚Äôt expect that at all, but that was really nice. Afterwards, we had their Mac N Cheese again, and everything was delivered on point. My wife and I both had their Filet Minon. I had their four-course meal, all of my servings was outstanding, as well as my wife‚Äôs.

We had the pleasure of meeting Greg, and it was an absolute pleasure. We will be back in the future, we really appreciated Greg and his restaurant.

Original Post: My wife and I came here 8/9/19, excited as we had tried Vintage Press and The Depot, both were terrific. We arrived around 7:15 PM, and were seated in the bar area because it was pretty busy. It took at least 10 minutes to get drinks ordered. Then after we had our drinks for another 10-15 minutes, our waitress came and took our order, she had intended just for us to order an appetizer, however we wanted to our food ordered since we could see things were taking a bit longer. After we waited for another 20 minutes, our appetizer, MAC and cheese was delivered, which was delicious. After we had finished, we waited another 30 minutes for our dinner to finally arrive. We were offered another round of drinks after our appetizer was finished, which we agreed, however those didn‚Äôt show up until after our dinner had been served. That was another extended length of time.

We understand a popular restaurant being busy, however the main reason for the 1 star rating was that my wagyu beef had terrible texture, firm on the outside but very rare on the inside. Also, there were pieces of fat bordering the edge of the cut. I found it pretty disappointing I couldn‚Äôt fully finish this $65 plate. Also, my wife‚Äôs chicken had blood in it. We had to google to see if it was even safe to eat. She ate very little in fear of food poisoning.

We also found it incredibly rude that our waitress had time to talk to people she knew personally, talking about texting them and going on about their personal lives, as our service had been pretty poor, along with our food.

I asked for the check and feared waiting any longer. Before tip it was $145. For the price of our drinks and meal, we were extremely disappointed.

We enjoyed the atmosphere and the appetizer, however I don‚Äôt think we‚Äôll be back for a return visit.</text>

<Pictures>None</Pictures><review>I can't believe there are no reviews for Jack and Charlie's!!! This is one of our favorite restaurants in Visalia. Classic, but basic, art nouveau design. If you are looking for true exciting, creative, market-fresh bistro-syle food, this is your place. Think Wolfgang Puck in the early days. I could go on and on about favorite dishes we have had there--unique appetizers that you won't find anywhere (I don't care where you go), foie gras, great fish dishes (depending on what is fresh), beef stroganoff made with steak and fresh noodles, steaks, fabulous bread pudding. Specially selected wines, unique bar drinks and a specialty in absinthes. Great bar scene. I hesitate to tell you how good this place really is as I selfishly don't want everyone to go.... The only disappointment about this restaurant is the menu sometimes changes---as it must---but the excitement of trying new dishes typically makes up for it.< /review>< response>
